doctype html
head
	meta(charset="utf-8")
	meta(name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1")
	title Owl. The game.
	link(rel="stylesheet" href="css/mainstyle.css")
body
	div.test-button Go

	div.container

		section.preloader
			div.preloader__spinner
			div.preloader__progress 0%

		section.main-menu
			div.main-menu__wrapper
				div.main-menu__overlay
				nav.main-menu__links
					div.main-menu__start-game Play
					div.main-menu__artefacts Artefacts
					div.main-menu__statistic Statistic
					div.main-menu__tutorial Tutorial

		section.game-levels 

		section.artefacts

		section.statistic
			div.statistic__wrapper
				div.statistic__hero
					div.statistic__title Owl
					div.statistic__health 
					div.statistic__damage 
					div.statistic__timer-bonus 
				div.statistic__game
					div.statistic__title Game
					div.statistic__pure-time 
					div.statistic__answers 
					div.statistic__mistakes 
					div.statistic__progress 
					div.statistic__best-result 
				div.statistic__buttons 
					div.statistic__log-button Check the log<span> &rarr;</span>
					div.statistic__restart-button Restart game
			div.statistic__log-wrapper
				div.statistic__title Log
				div.output.statistic__log-output
					div.output__note Details of each new level will be here.

		section.tutorial
			div.tutorial__wrapper
				div.page
					div.page__title Owl 
					div.page__wrapper
						div.page__text
							| This is simple single-player game created using frontend development tools.
							| The main goal of this progect is to gain practical developer skills.  
							| Practice is the only way to realize how programming actually works.
							div.page__skip-button Skip <span> &rarr;</span>
				div.page.page_hidden_away
					div.page__title Gameplay
					div.page__wrapper
						div.page__text 
							| You have to play as Owl character defeating enemies.
							| There are 8 levels in this game. To complite a level you have to solve simple
							| tasks choosing the right answer in time. 
				div.page.page_hidden_away
					div.page__title Tasks 
					div.page__wrapper
						div.page__text
							| Tasks appear every 5 seconds. Spheres with different answers will be shown next. 
							| Just click the sphere which contains 
							| the right answer as you suppose.  
				div.page.page_hidden_away
					div.page__title Damage
					div.page__wrapper
						div.page__text
							| Each right answer allows you to wound the enemy depending on 
							| the Owl's damage, and wrong answer allows the enemy to do the same. The end of 
							| time is a wrong answer. The tasks appear until the Owl or enemy's health points are zero.
				div.page.page_hidden_away
					div.page__title Coins
					div.page__wrapper
						div.page__text
							| If the level is successfully complited
							| you will get several coins. Otherwise you will lose 15% of your current coins.
							| You can spend these coins to buy some artefacts if you need it. 
				div.page.page_hidden_away
					div.page__title Artefacts
					div.page__wrapper
						div.page__text
							| There are 3 types of artefacts: 
							| health increase, damage increase and timer bonus. All current statistic you can see in the 
							| Statistic section. 
				div.page.page_hidden_away
					div.page__title Let's play  
					div.page__wrapper
						div.page__text
							| Here we go. Try it and enjoy the game. 
							div.page__play-button Play <span> &rarr;</span>

			div.tutorial__next &rarr;
			div.tutorial__prev &larr;
		
		nav.control-panel
			div.control-panel__back-button &larr;
			div.control-panel__data
					

		section.battle-field
			div.battle-field__wound
			div.battle-field__wrapper
				div.timer 
				div.task 
				div.spheres-area
				div.battle-field__bars
					div.hp-bar.hp-bar_bind_hero
						div.hp-bar__current
						div.hp-bar__text

					div.hp-bar.hp-bar_bind_enemy
						div.hp-bar__current
						div.hp-bar__text 
				

		section.outro
			div.outro__wrapper
				div.outro__stats
					div.outro__coins 
				div.outro__composition
					div.outro__stains
					div.outro__image


	script(src="js/mainscript.js")